#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn24.18"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn24.18:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 24 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 24 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.18:0.2"
msgid "1. Sotāpattivagga "
msgstr "1. Stream-Entry "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn24.18:0.3"
msgid "18. Nevahotinanahotitathāgatosutta "
msgstr "18. A Realized One Neither Exists Nor Doesn’t Exist "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn24.18:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.18:1.2"
msgid "“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya, kiṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati: "
msgstr "“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on what, does the view arise: "

msgctxt "sn24.18:1.3"
msgid "‘neva hoti, na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’”ti? "
msgstr "‘A Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist after death’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.18:1.4"
msgid "“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe … "
msgstr "“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn24.18:2.1"
msgid "“Rūpe kho, bhikkhave, sati, rūpaṃ upādāya, rūpaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati: "
msgstr "“When form exists, because of grasping form and insisting on form, the view arises: "

msgctxt "sn24.18:2.2"
msgid "‘neva hoti, na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’”ti … pe …. "
msgstr "‘A Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist after death’ … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn24.18:3.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn24.18:3.2"
msgid "rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "Is form permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.18:3.3"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe … "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” … "

msgctxt "sn24.18:3.4"
msgid "vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya: "
msgstr "“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would the view arise: "

msgctxt "sn24.18:3.5"
msgid "‘neva hoti, na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’”ti? "
msgstr "‘A Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist after death’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.18:3.6"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.18:3.7"
msgid "“Yampidaṃ diṭṭhaṃ sutaṃ mutaṃ viññātaṃ pattaṃ pariyesitaṃ anuvicaritaṃ manasā tampi niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "“That which is seen, heard, thought, known, sought, and explored by the mind: is that permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.18:3.8"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.18:3.9"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.18:3.10"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.18:3.11"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya: "
msgstr "“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would the view arise: "

msgctxt "sn24.18:3.12"
msgid "‘neva hoti, na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’”ti? "
msgstr "‘A Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist after death’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.18:3.13"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.217, sc4
msgctxt "sn24.18:4.1"
msgid "“Yato kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvakassa imesu ca ṭhānesu kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti, dukkhepissa kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti, dukkhasamudayepissa kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti, dukkhanirodhepissa kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti, dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāyapissa kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti—"
msgstr "“When a noble disciple has given up doubt in these six cases, and has given up doubt in suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation, "

msgctxt "sn24.18:4.2"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako sotāpanno avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyano”ti. "
msgstr "they’re called a noble disciple who is a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.” "

msgctxt "sn24.18:4.3"
msgid "Aṭṭhārasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn24.18:4.4"
msgid "Sotāpattivaggo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn24.18:4.5"
msgid "Aṭṭhārasaveyyākaraṇaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn24.18:5.1"
msgid "Vātaṃ etaṃ mama, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn24.18:5.2"
msgid "so attā no ca me siyā; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn24.18:5.3"
msgid "Natthi karoto hetu ca, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn24.18:5.4"
msgid "mahādiṭṭhena aṭṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn24.18:6.1"
msgid "Sassato loko ca, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn24.18:6.2"
msgid "Asassato ca antavā ca; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn24.18:6.3"
msgid "Anantavā ca taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīranti, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn24.18:6.4"
msgid "Aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīranti ca. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn24.18:7.1"
msgid "Hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn24.18:7.2"
msgid "Na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn24.18:7.3"
msgid "Neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
